<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="35" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="18.[136,1452,1247,1778]" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,488,1535,1562]" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[495,523,1536,1562]" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">—</emphasis>
The species is found in all regions of 
<collectingCountry box="[959,1030,1535,1561]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, associated with all phytogeographic domains and is found in disturbed areas, altitude fields, seasonal forest, costal forest and rocky outcrops (BFG 2018, 
<bibRefCitation author="Flora do Brasil" box="[136,372,1607,1634]" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" refId="ref15971" refString="Flora do Brasil 2020 (2020) Fabaceae. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. [http: // reflora. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 115]" type="url" year="2020">
Flora do 
<collectingCountry box="[237,304,1607,1633]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Brasil</collectingCountry>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). In the study area, it was collected at the edge of the fragment, at 
<specimenCount box="[1114,1192,1608,1634]" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" type="generic">
<quantity box="[1114,1188,1608,1634]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" unit="m" value="900.0">900 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[136,1452,1247,1778]" box="[189,741,1643,1670]" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,1644,1670]" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Registered with flowers in August.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[136,1452,1247,1778]" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,487,1679,1705]" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Taxonomic discussion:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. S. Irwin &amp; Barneby" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[486,682,1679,1706]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obtusifolia">
<emphasis box="[486,682,1679,1706]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Senna obtusifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized, mainly, by the subshrubby habit, 6–leaflet leaves with nectary stipitate in the raque, axillary raceme, yellow corolla flowers and by the vegetable 
<typeStatus box="[1210,1258,1716,1742]" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">type</typeStatus>
fruit. Among the 
<taxonomicName box="[136,292,1751,1778]" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis box="[136,204,1752,1778]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Senna</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the studied area, it was the only one that presented 6–foliolate leaves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
